heaviest_rainfall.status: On 04 January 2025, a record rainfall of 36.8mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  4.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today ranked 10th for the heaviest rainfall ever in our records, with a peak intensity of 10.1mm per hour sustained for 16.6 hours, resulting in a total accumulation of 9.37mm.  On 02 September 2025, the rain fell at an exceptional rate, peaking at 27.0mm per hour, the heaviest downpour recorded.  A total of 21.19mm fell over the 15.0 hour storm.

longest_rain.status: Ranked 10th for lengthiest precipitation event, today's storm spanned 16.6 hours and was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 10.1mm per hour.  9.37mm of rain fell in total.  Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.
